## Painting considerations for Srinagar homes

Kashmir's climate affects how and when to paint. High humidity during rainy weeks slows drying and can cause bubbling if walls are damp. Winter's cold can extend curing times for exterior work. Many Srinagar homeowners plan interior painting in spring or early autumn and reserve exterior jobs for drier months.

Surface type varies widely — old lime plaster, cement render, wood panelling, and modern gypsum boards each need different preparation. Homes near Dal Lake or in low-lying areas may have moisture issues that require anti-fungal primer before painting. Mention any known damp spots or previous peeling when booking so your painter arrives with the right products.

Furniture protection is part of professional painting. Partners cover floors, move or wrap furniture where possible, and clean up after the job. For occupied homes, discuss which rooms to paint in sequence so your household can keep using essential spaces during a multi-day project.

