## Tips before your painting visit

Help your project start smoothly:

- **Choose colours in advance** — have shade codes or sample pots ready for the consultation.
- **Clear walls** — remove frames, clocks, and shelves from rooms being painted.
- **Cover or move valuables** — even professional painters appreciate clear floor space.
- **Ventilate after interior work** — open windows when weather allows to speed drying and reduce odour.
- **Inspect before final payment** — check edges, corners, and ceiling lines in daylight before signing off.

For touch-ups, mark the exact spots needing work with tape or photos so the painter addresses everything in one visit. For full repaints, agree on number of coats and whether ceilings are included.

